---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Montenegro Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/montenegro/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Croatia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/croatia' },
  { title: 'Greece for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/greece' },
  { title: 'Albania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/albania' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'montenegroFit', header: 'Montenegro Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€260-370/mo', montenegroFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€310-440/mo', montenegroFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€240-340/mo', montenegroFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€220-320/mo', montenegroFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local Insurers', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: '€50-150/mo', montenegroFit: 'Basic Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€240-370', annual: '€2,880-4,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€340-500', annual: '€4,080-6,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€450-680', annual: '€5,400-8,160' },
  { category: 'Montenegro Public', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Limited access for expats' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: '€30-80/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Montenegro 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Montenegro. Adriatic coast, Bay of Kotor, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Montenegro"
  subheadline="Montenegro offers dramatic Adriatic coast, Bay of Kotor beauty, affordable living, and emerging expat community—a hidden gem for budget-conscious retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/montenegro-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Montenegro</h2>
  <p>
    Montenegro punches above its weight—stunning Adriatic coastline, dramatic mountains, the UNESCO Bay of Kotor, and remarkably affordable living. It's Croatia's neighbor without the crowds or prices. EU candidate status means improving standards while costs remain low.
  </p>

  <p>
    The Bay of Kotor (Kotor, Tivat, Herceg Novi) offers Mediterranean living with dramatic mountain backdrop. Budva provides beach resort life. The north has mountains, monasteries, and extreme affordability. Podgorica is the practical capital with improving facilities.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Basic public; private improving in coastal areas</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Montenegrin/Serbian; English in tourist areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,000-2,000/month; very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean coast; continental interior</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Candidate; uses EUR unofficially</li>
      <li><strong>Highlight:</strong> Bay of Kotor—Mediterranean fjord</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Montenegro's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Montenegro has public healthcare, but quality is limited—facilities are dated, equipment older, and English uncommon. The best public hospitals are in Podgorica. Private healthcare is developing, particularly in coastal tourist areas serving expats and visitors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private clinics in Kotor, Tivat, and Budva offer adequate care for routine needs. For serious conditions, many travel to Croatia (Dubrovnik, Zagreb) or further. International insurance with evacuation coverage is essential—local healthcare simply isn't adequate for complex senior care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Healthcare Limitations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Montenegro's healthcare is not suited for seniors with serious medical needs. Private clinics handle routine issues but complex care requires travel. Dubrovnik, Croatia is 2 hours away with better facilities. International insurance with evacuation to EU hospitals is essential.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Montenegro offers welcoming options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence (Property/Income)</h3>
  <p>
    Owning property in Montenegro or demonstrating sufficient income (typically €500+/month) allows temporary residence application. Valid 1 year, renewable. Process is relatively straightforward.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities (including US, UK, EU) can stay visa-free for 90 days, exit briefly, and return. While not formal residence, many retirees use this approach for extended stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After 5 years of temporary residence, you can apply for permanent residence. This provides more stability and easier access to services.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Montenegro:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Health insurance typically required</li>
    <li><strong>Quality:</strong> Local healthcare limitations mean international essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Must include evacuation to EU for serious care</li>
    <li><strong>Travel:</strong> Coverage for Croatia and EU medical travel important</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Montenegro</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential—not optional—for Montenegro. Local healthcare isn't adequate for serious senior care. Ensure your plan includes: evacuation to EU hospitals, coverage in Croatia (common medical destination), and adequate specialist coverage. Don't rely on local options alone.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Montenegro, international coverage with evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Montenegro</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Evacuation included, EU hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good Balkans region coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Croatian Healthcare:</strong> Accessible for treatment (Dubrovnik 2hrs)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare international coverage essential for Montenegro's healthcare limitations.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Montenegro are affordable, but international coverage is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local care is cheap; high deductible for serious issues</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash locally:</strong> Private clinics €30-80/visit; easy cash payment</li>
    <li><strong>Balkans coverage:</strong> Plans covering Montenegro + Croatia efficiently</li>
    <li><strong>Don't skimp:</strong> Evacuation coverage is essential, not optional</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Budget Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month Social Security. Seeking Mediterranean value.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with evacuation. Lives in Bay of Kotor. Private clinics for routine; Croatia for complex.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€290/month insurance. Lives comfortably on €1,000/month remaining. Excellent value.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Property Owner, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Bought apartment in Tivat. Pension £1,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with worldwide coverage. Uses Porto Montenegro clinic locally. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~€420/month. Comfortable coastal Mediterranean life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German Sailing Enthusiast, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Keeps boat in Bay of Kotor. Splits time Montenegro/Germany. Pension €2,000/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global covering Europe. Uses German system at home. Montenegro private locally.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~€350/month. Perfect for two-base lifestyle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Montenegro safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally yes. Montenegro is peaceful with low crime. Tourist areas are well-policed. Organized crime exists but rarely affects expats. The main safety concern is actually driving—mountain roads can be challenging. Overall, it's a safe retirement destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get by with English?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        In tourist areas (Kotor, Tivat, Budva) yes—many speak English. Outside tourist zones, it's limited. Younger Montenegrins often speak English; older generation less so. Serbian/Montenegrin basics help significantly. Healthcare outside private clinics may require translation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Montenegro compare to Croatia?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Montenegro is significantly cheaper (40-50% less), less crowded, more raw. Croatia has better healthcare, more developed infrastructure, EU membership. Montenegro offers better value; Croatia offers more polish. Many choose Montenegro for cost and consider Croatia for medical care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the healthcare limitations?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Take them seriously. Montenegro is not the place for seniors with serious ongoing medical needs. Routine care is manageable; complex care requires travel. Dubrovnik (Croatia) is 2 hours away with better hospitals. For major issues, expect evacuation to Croatia or EU. Plan accordingly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with evacuation coverage essential for Montenegro.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Montenegrin authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
